XI. 1. nonum superantis annum: see on P. 24. The separated nonum emphasizes the excellence of the wine. The group nonum superantis annum forms a compound adjective3 hence the grouping from nonum to cadus is that of P. 9.

3. nectendis (ps) i.e. ‘sor the weaving (of garlands)'; see on P. 26.

4. hederae (p) i.e. ‘there is ivy (in plenty)'; see on P. 38, and P. 35.

5. multa (pp) has emphasis3 see also on Odes 4. 9. 26.

6, 7. ara...verbenis: for the grouping see on P. 14.

7, 8. immolato (ps) i.e. ‘with the sacrifice (ofa lamb)'; see P. 26 and 21. Compare Odes 1. 19. 16.

9. cuncta (s) i.e. ‘the whole without exception'; see too P. 21.
